2 Garlic
1 packet Slivered Almonds
1 sachet Chilli Flakes
1 packet Parsley
1 Baby Broccoli
1 Lemon
20 g butter
1 drizzle olive oil

• Halve any thicker stalks of baby broccoli lengthways. Zest lemon to get a
pinch and slice into wedges. Finely chop parsley and garlic.

• Heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat. Toast almonds, tossing,
until golden, 2-3 minutes. Transfer to a bowl.
• Return frying pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• Cook baby broccoli, until tender, 5-6 minutes.

• Reduce heat to medium, then add the butter, garlic, chilli flakes (if using),
parsley, lemon zest and a generous squeeze of lemon juice. Cook, tossing
until fragrant, 1 minute. Season with salt and pepper.

• Transfer garlicky baby broccoli to a serving plate.
• Garnish with toasted almonds to serve. Enjoy!